Test: Coverage

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

2021-01-27

Source: vignettes/tests/test_coverage.Rmd
test_coverage.Rmd
library(testthat)
library(matrixR)
context("Test Coverage.")
A <- matrix(
  data = 1:10,
  ncol = 2
)
test_that("nonsquare matrix", {
  expect_false(
    is_sqr(A)
  )
  expect_false(
    is_posdef(A)
  )
  expect_false(
    is_inv(A)
  )
  expect_false(
    is_diag(A)
  )
  expect_error(
    low2sym(A)
  )
  expect_error(
    up2sym(A)
  )
  expect_error(
    ones(dim(A)[1], dim(A)[2])
  )
  expect_error(
    ones_from(A)
  )
  expect_false(
    is_nilpot(A)
  )
  expect_false(
    is_idempot(A)
  )
  expect_error(
    pow(A, 0)
  )
  expect_error(
    tr(A)
  )
})

B <- matrix(
  data = "text",
  nrow = 2,
  ncol = 2
)
test_that("nonnumeric", {
  expect_error(
    is_sqr(B)
  )
})

test_that("vector", {
  expect_error(
    is_sqr(C)
  )
})

D <- matrix(
  data = c(1, 2, 2, 1),
  ncol = 2
)
v <- c(1, 2)
test_that("Cor2Cov - is_posdef", {
  expect_error(
    Cor2Cov(D, v)
  )
})
#> Test passed ðŸŽŠ
test_that("Cov2Cor - is_posdef", {
  expect_error(
    Cov2Cor(D)
  )
})
#> Test passed ðŸŽŠ
E <- matrix(
  data = c(
    1,
    .5,
    .5,
    1
  ),
  ncol = 2
)
u <- c(-1, 1)
test_that("Cor2Cov - v is positive", {
  expect_error(
    Cor2Cov(E, u)
  )
})
